Sentencas: The mass/charge transfer characteristics in a simulated MOLB (mono-block-layer built)-type solid-oxide fuel cells have been studied numerically.
Titulo: Mass/Charge Transfer in Mono-Block-Layer-Built-Type Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The transport phenomena within a linear MOLB module, including flow channels, active porous electrodes, electrolyte, and interconnections, are simulated using the finite volume method.
Titulo: Mass/Charge Transfer in Mono-Block-Layer-Built-Type Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The gas flow in the porous electrodes is governed by the isotropic linear resistance model with constant porosity and permeability.
Titulo: Mass/Charge Transfer in Mono-Block-Layer-Built-Type Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The diffusions of reactant species in the porous electrodes are described by the Stefan-Maxwell relation.
Titulo: Mass/Charge Transfer in Mono-Block-Layer-Built-Type Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Effective diffusivities for porous layers follow the Bruggman model.
Titulo: Mass/Charge Transfer in Mono-Block-Layer-Built-Type Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Porous electrochemistry is depicted via surface reactions with a constant surface-to-volume ratio, tortuosity, and average pore size.
Titulo: Mass/Charge Transfer in Mono-Block-Layer-Built-Type Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Results of the cathode-supported cell and the anode-supported cell are obtained, discussed, and compared thereafter for the first time.
Titulo: Mass/Charge Transfer in Mono-Block-Layer-Built-Type Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells
